1. DVWA was installed on the Metasploitable2 virtual machine.
2. DVWA security level was set to LOW.
3. The target IP address was identified using `ip a`.
4. The DVWA web application was accessed from Kali Linux.
5. Manual SQL Injection testing was performed.
6. Automated SQL Injection testing was done using sqlmap.
7. Reflected XSS vulnerability was tested using payloads.
8. Burp Suite was configured with Firefox to intercept requests.
9. Authentication mechanisms were verified.
10. All findings were documented with screenshots.

